        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 10:31PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1030 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 5 miles northwest of Felt, or 18 miles west of Boise
City, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boise City, Texline, Keyes, Kenton, Wheeless, Black Mesa Park, and
Felt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
